definitions: act of following movements or progress of something over time
marks or traces left by movement through an area
examples: The wildlife tracking revealed the deer's migration patterns
Package tracking shows your order will arrive tomorrow
The fresh tracking in the snow led to the lost hikers
Bear tracking was visible along the muddy riverbank

definitions: large stretch or area of land with common features
connected system of organs serving specific bodily function
short pamphlet or booklet on religious or political topic
examples: They purchased a fifty-acre tract for the new development
The desert tract stretched endlessly toward the horizon
The digestive tract processes food from mouth to intestines
Infections in the respiratory tract can cause breathing difficulties
Religious tracts were distributed outside the train station
Political tracts from the revolution are preserved in museums

definitions: grip between tire and road surface preventing slipping
medical treatment using steady pulling force on body part
process of gaining acceptance support or popularity for idea
examples: The car lost traction on the icy mountain road
Winter tires provide better traction in snowy conditions
The patient required traction to realign the broken leg
Spinal traction helped relieve pressure on compressed discs
The new policy is finally gaining traction with voters
Their startup idea gained traction after the media coverage

definitions: powerful motor vehicle with large rear wheels for pulling farm equipment
examples: The farmer drove the tractor across the freshly plowed field
Modern tractors have air-conditioned cabins and GPS systems

definitions: traditional folk music especially Irish or British folk music
examples: The pub features live trad music every Friday night
She learned to play trad tunes on her grandfather's fiddle

definitions: legally registered symbol or name identifying company products
distinctive characteristic or feature regularly associated with person
examples: The company filed to protect its trademark in multiple countries
Using someone else's trademark without permission is illegal
Her trademark smile appeared in every photograph
The director's trademark style includes long tracking shots

definitions: situation where you accept something bad to get something good
examples: The tradeoff between work and family time troubled him
There's always a tradeoff between quality and affordability

definitions: person who buys and sells goods or financial instruments
examples: The stock trader monitored market movements throughout the day
Local traders gathered at the weekly farmers market

definitions: person skilled in particular manual trade requiring special training
examples: The tradesman carefully installed the custom kitchen cabinets
Local tradesmen were hired to restore the historic building

definitions: philosophy or attitude that values maintaining established customs beliefs and practices
examples: His traditionalism conflicted with the company's innovative culture

definitions: person who supports maintaining traditional values methods or practices
examples: The traditionalist opposed changes to the historic building's facade

definitions: person who illegally trades or deals in prohibited goods
examples: Police arrested the suspected drug trafficker at the border

definitions: dramatic work containing both tragic and comic elements in balance
examples: Shakespeare's tragicomedy blends humor with serious philosophical themes
Life itself often feels like a tragicomedy of errors

definitions: person who makes new track through wild country or introduces innovations
examples: She was a trailblazer in the male-dominated tech industry

definitions: point where hiking trail begins usually marked with signs
examples: We met at the trailhead before dawn to start hiking
The trailhead parking lot fills quickly on weekend mornings

definitions: act of following behind someone or something at distance
plant growth that hangs down or spreads along ground
examples: The detective spent hours trailing the suspected criminal
Children were trailing behind their teacher on the field trip

She chose trailing plants for the hanging baskets

definitions: person who is learning job or skill through instruction
examples: The trainee shadowed experienced staff for two weeks

definitions: person who betrays trust loyalty or allegiance especially to country
examples: The traitor sold military secrets to enemy agents

definitions: curved path followed by object moving through space
path course or progression of something over time
examples: Scientists calculated the meteor's trajectory through Earth's atmosphere

definitions: passenger vehicle running on rails through city streets

definitions: single car of tram system for transporting passengers
examples: The vintage tramcar has been restored to its original colors
Tourists love riding the tramcar up the steep hills

definitions: track or route followed by trams in urban transport system
examples: New tramlines will connect the suburbs to downtown
Workers are repairing the damaged tramline near the station

definitions: person who travels from place to place without home or job
sound or act of walking with heavy steps
examples: The old tramp asked for spare change outside the station

We heard the tramp of boots marching down the corridor
The tramp through muddy fields left everyone exhausted

examples: The trampling of flowers upset the garden club members

definitions: strong fabric sheet connected by springs to frame for jumping
examples: Children spent hours jumping on the backyard trampoline

definitions: system of trams or cable cars for passenger transport

definitions: half-conscious state with reduced awareness of surroundings often induced
examples: The hypnotist put volunteers into a deep therapeutic trance

definitions: portion of something especially money divided into parts
examples: The loan will be released in three tranches over two years

definitions: quality or state of being calm peaceful and untroubled

definitions: drug used to reduce anxiety or agitation in humans or animals

definitions: quality or state of being calm peaceful and untroubled
examples: The garden's tranquillity made it perfect for quiet reflection

definitions: state of being or experience beyond normal physical or material existence

definitions: written or typed copy of spoken words from recording or proceedings

definitions: process of converting spoken words or music into written form

examples: Medical transcription requires excellent listening and typing skills

definitions: device that converts one form of energy into another form

definitions: process of converting one form of signal or energy into another
examples: Signal transduction allows cells to respond to their environment

definitions: part of church crossing main body at right angles forming cross shape

definitions: act of moving or shifting something from one place to another

examples: The transference of property ownership requires legal documentation

definitions: complete change of form or appearance into more beautiful or spiritual state
examples: The artist captured the transfiguration of caterpillar into butterfly

definitions: electrical device that changes voltage of alternating current

definitions: medical procedure transferring blood from donor into patient's bloodstream
examples: The accident victim needed an emergency blood transfusion

definitions: quality of lasting only for short time being temporary or fleeting

definitions: semiconductor device used to amplify or switch electronic signals

definitions: electronic device that sends out radio or television signals
